Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.82,0:00:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.40,0:00:15.37,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,To think something like this would happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.37,0:00:18.23,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's no use, Mr. Glover.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.23,0:00:20.37,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I have one of these too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.25,0:00:27.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that, the magistrate's office'll happily arrest you for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.00,0:00:30.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that happens, the business and the Satchō Alliance'll be over.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.95,0:00:38.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry! I, Sakamoto Ryōma, shall clear any doubts on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.93,0:00:45.02,Thoughts,,10,10,0,,{\be10}Vivid summer memories surpass their season to solve mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.02,0:00:47.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A Bakumatsu period drama set in Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.11,0:00:49.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Where is the missing scriptwriter?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.08,0:00:50.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.68,0:00:52.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.92,0:00:54.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.09,0:02:51.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Did we travel back in time?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.65,0:02:53.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.37,0:03:03.91,Signs,,0,0,0,,Nagasaki Station
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nagasaki Station
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.25,0:03:06.92,Signs,,0,0,0,,Nagasaki Confucius Shrine · Historical Museum of China
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.29,0:03:10.13,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ōura Church
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.50,0:03:13.13,Signs,,0,0,0,,Glover Garden
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.72,0:02:58.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As usual, Ran drew first prize in the shopping district's lottery,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.58,0:03:03.91,Thoughts,,0,0,15,,{\be10}so today, we've come to Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.88,0:03:14.37,Thoughts,,0,0,17,,{\be10}This is Glover Garden, where Thomas Blake Glover,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.37,0:03:20.16,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}an English{Scottish, but they say English} merchant who supported Shishi like Sakamoto Ryōma in the Bakumatsu period once lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.16,0:03:22.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's the most famous place in Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.91,0:03:26.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's she looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.65,0:03:29.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The heart stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.48,0:03:30.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heart stones?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.81,0:03:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two of the paving stones in the Garden are shaped like hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.33,0:03:39.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's all sorts of legends about them,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.22,0:03:44.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,such as 'if a couple finds them they'll be married', and 'if you touch them your love will come true'.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.04,0:03:46.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.00,0:03:47.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.04,0:03:49.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now where's the other one?{I wonder where the other is? -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.27,0:03:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never mind that, I want to try Nagasaki's famous {\i1}Champon{\i0} and {\i1}Sara{\i0} {\i1}Udon{\i0}—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.89,0:03:57.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.53,0:04:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What was that just now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:02.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they said 'Murderer!'...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.98,0:04:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.89,0:04:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Out the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.58,0:04:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody move!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.67,0:04:14.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can leave the rest to the great detective Kogorō Mouri...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.07,0:04:17.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with this victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.01,0:04:21.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He came back to life!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.16,0:04:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who exactly are yo—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.85,0:04:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.90,0:04:35.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I didn't make it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.24,0:04:37.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.94,0:04:39.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyone'd get misled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.05,0:04:47.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What was going on here was filming a 2-hour TV mystery drama based in the Nagasaki of the Bakumatsu period.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.35,0:04:51.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A murder occurs in the Glover Residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.24,0:04:55.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sakamoto Ryōma, who was hiding in the Residence, takes on a detective role,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.26,0:04:58.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}aided by the young female doctor of Western Medicine, Ine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.34,0:05:04.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sets out to solve the case to clear the doubts people have of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.74,0:05:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about it, Ine?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.08,0:05:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was a pistol used after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.12,0:05:12.17,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kyōnosuke Sasahara (33)\NAs Sakamoto Ryōma
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.65,0:05:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think something like this would happen in our mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.88,0:05:18.67,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Benichiyo Yamashita (42)\NAs Tsuru
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.67,0:05:21.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's unfortunate for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.55,0:05:24.68,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Andrew Hatta (50)\NAs Glover
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.56,0:05:29.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no mistake. He was killed by a pistol.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.43,0:05:32.69,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Futaba Nanao (23)\NAs Karasuma Ine
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.69,0:05:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cut! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.09,0:05:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, was that really okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.40,0:05:42.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A temporary doctor shouldn't show that much emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.07,0:05:44.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.40,0:05:47.12,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Keisuke Sakakibara (45)\NTV Drama director
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.12,0:05:47.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ine's a novice doctor, so it makes sense for her to be emotional.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.12,0:05:50.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,O-Chiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s acting was great as always too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.41,0:05:50.45,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Akikazu Nakane (48)\NCameraman
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.45,0:05:53.54,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,T-That's right, Benichiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.70,0:05:53.75,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ryūhei Kishimura (30)\NAssistant Director
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.41,0:05:56.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that right? Then it'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.59,0:06:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm... next up is the scene where the victim's\Nmerchant friend, Soneya Chūbee, first appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.59,0:06:07.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.19,0:06:08.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.35,0:06:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Treat me well, Bara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.14,0:06:14.23,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Chōjirō Sazanami (45)\NAs Soneya Chūbee
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.23,0:06:17.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure. I'm counting on you, Chō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.27,0:06:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are Soneya's props?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.44,0:06:19.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.73,0:06:22.82,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,They're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.02,0:06:22.82,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kazuomi Sakota (35)\NProp Master
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.42,0:06:29.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this a bit over-the-top?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.24,0:06:30.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.77,0:06:32.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you do something about this comb too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.66,0:06:36.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But... but those are from 'Madame Butterfly'...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.69,0:06:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An opera lover as always, Sakota.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.80,0:06:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is this really okay, Bara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.45,0:06:46.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we really start filming without even\Nknowing the end, or should I say, the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.51,0:06:52.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, even if it's a bit late, it'll be a masterpiece. This {\i1}is{\i0} Tatsumi we're talking about here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.39,0:06:57.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's quite a beauty, that girl playing the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.98,0:07:00.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that Futaba Nanao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.53,0:07:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's a new actress thought to be getting her break soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.05,0:07:07.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't give me that! I can't just ignore it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.98,0:07:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I said, it'll be really bad, so make sure you cover it up...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.24,0:07:20.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard from Sonoko that Sasahara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s a handsome bachelor who's a regular among most-wanted boyfriend rankings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.66,0:07:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what's happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.98,0:07:25.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}(Gesture referring to love in Japan)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.98,0:07:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmph. Maybe it's trouble related to {\i1}this{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.27,0:07:27.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.44,0:07:29.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're in trouble!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.89,0:07:32.76,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Taizō Ōki (52)\NDrama Production Company Producer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.00,0:07:32.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,T-T-Tatsumi's run off on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.90,0:07:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I knew he'd been stuck lately, but still...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.69,0:07:46.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though his old friends are all here for the first time in ages...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.74,0:07:48.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a bit longer and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.60,0:07:50.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Argh! I'm at my limit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:53.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your limit, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.05,0:07:54.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.46,0:07:56.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.94,0:07:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.49,0:08:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.90,0:08:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sleeping Kogorō?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.93,0:08:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.10,0:08:07.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I beg you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.56,0:08:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great detective Sleeping Kogorō, please deduce who the culprit is in this mystery drama!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.43,0:08:14.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.42,0:08:16.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.02,0:08:23.31,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kōsaku Tatsumi (45)\NScriptwriter
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.40,0:08:24.36,Thoughts,,10,10,0,,{\be10\an8}This mystery drama's scriptwriter, Kōsaku Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}, is a veteran whose scripts have won various prizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.13,0:08:28.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This drama isn't an adaptation, but an original work by Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.86,0:08:32.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and the writing's taking too long, causing the filming to begin with an unfinished script.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.41,0:08:38.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So the upcoming developments, not to mention the culprit of the case in the drama, are unknown to all but Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.87,0:08:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this drama goes belly up, it'll wreck our company!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.80,0:08:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you can at least spot the culprit, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I'll manage the rest somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.23,0:08:53.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.50,0:09:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought, it's impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.00,0:09:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The script's not even half-finished, so no matter how much they ask, to spot a culprit from this is just too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:11.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you took the job anyway, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.29,0:09:14.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying there's no riddle that Sleeping Kogorō can't solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.78,0:09:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.45,0:09:19.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}True, there aren't enough clues...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.95,0:09:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.79,0:09:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.67,0:09:28.92,Signs,,0,0,0,,Serial Art Theft Case
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.85,0:09:33.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're these?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.45,0:09:35.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are they here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.20,0:09:37.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A group of art thieves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.14,0:09:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! So there was a real case it was based on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.60,0:09:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the culprit is the group of thieves?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.57,0:09:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they don't appear up in the current script at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.92,0:09:50.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because it he hadn't put them in yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.91,0:09:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.82,0:09:56.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If so, they wouldn't be hidden by being stuck up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.66,0:10:00.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, right. I'm leaving now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.75,0:10:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you've gotta do something about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.94,0:10:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd this happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.79,0:10:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm worn out!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.26,0:10:16.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the end, we didn't find many clues at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.68,0:10:21.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you, the culprit's the group of thieves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.12,0:10:22.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.00,0:10:29.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm Andrew Hatta, the actor playing Glover.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.83,0:10:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't my real face look just like\Nthe Glover statue in Glover Garden?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.07,0:10:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.46,0:10:45.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Though when Glover was working with Ryōma, he was only 30 years old...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.70,0:10:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Detective Boy{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.82,0:10:53.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were thinking that the actor's much older than the real Glover was, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.24,0:10:54.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.13,0:11:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The management are going through trouble at Ōki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s production company.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.60,0:11:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why, thanks to Ōki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Sakakibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s connections,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.56,0:11:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,most of the actors this time are\Nworking for lower pay than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.55,0:11:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that you are too, Andrew{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.34,0:11:15.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. We go back a long way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.99,0:11:20.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The director{{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}} said that old friends had gathered for the first time in ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.23,0:11:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.43,0:11:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakakibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Ōki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, O-Chiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and I've worked together since the days before we became popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.32,0:11:33.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} too, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.87,0:11:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.14,0:11:39.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They hadn't cast anyone for the role of Glover but me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.86,0:11:46.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so they decided that we'd be a middle-aged couple, with me already married to Tsuru.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.14,0:11:49.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't agree with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.76,0:11:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was someone who liked to respect reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.11,0:11:56.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So is that why he abandoned the script and vanished?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.63,0:11:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.78,0:12:03.49,Signs,,0,0,0,,Dutch Slope
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.83,0:12:07.25,Signs,,0,0,0,,Higashiyamate No.13
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.29,0:12:12.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Kogorō told me to ask you just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.14,0:12:15.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know. How about you, Bara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.72,0:12:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me neither. Finding bits of info was a secret hobby of Tatsumi's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.81,0:12:28.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what're you doing?! It's only a matter of time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.55,0:12:43.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.51,0:12:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the kid who was with Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, aren't you? {stopping here for today}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.93,0:12:58.81,Signs,,0,0,0,,Nagasaki Museum of History and Culture
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.81,0:13:00.81,Signs,,0,0,0,,In 1582,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.81,0:13:00.81,Signs,,0,0,0,,the Tenshō embassy to Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.81,0:13:00.81,Signs,,0,0,0,,left Nagasaki
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.81,0:13:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, Futaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} says she was born in Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.75,0:13:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since my parts in the current script are all done filming,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.03,0:13:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I could help you by being a guide...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.70,0:13:14.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's a big help.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.85,0:13:17.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Visiting famous places with a beautiful actress tour guide!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.58,0:13:19.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Running your mouth off again, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.16,0:13:23.46,Signs,,0,0,0,,Site of Kameyama Shachū
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.95,0:13:23.95,Thoughts,,0,0,17,,{\be10}We visited the places related to the notes and photos
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.95,0:13:26.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}that Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} made when creating this drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.96,0:13:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This pistol's the one Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.96,0:13:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.26,0:13:36.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kazagashira Park - Statue of Sakamoto Ryōma
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.60,0:13:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,15,,'The dawn of Japan is close!'
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.63,0:13:41.98,Dialogue,,0,0,15,,In Nagasaki, we call kites{tako} 'flags{hata}'.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.31,0:13:41.98,Signs,,0,0,15,,Nagasaki 'Flag' Archive
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.27,0:13:45.81,Signs,,0,0,15,,Spectacles Bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.10,0:13:44.73,Dialogue,,0,0,17,,Ah, that's Spectacles Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.98,0:13:48.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, gimme yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.46,0:13:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, how interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.49,0:13:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, give them back!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.00,0:13:58.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.28,0:13:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.62,0:14:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man, I'm so hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.37,0:14:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.00,0:14:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be! It's Sleeping Kogorō!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.55,0:14:13.76,Signs,,0,0,0,,Shikairō
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.01,0:14:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,15,,This is the shop that invented {\i1}Champon{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.76,0:14:15.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to eating it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.39,0:14:19.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their {\i1}Sara{\i0} {\i1}Udon{\i0}'s pretty tasty, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.64,0:14:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That thing's cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.70,0:14:24.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.94,0:14:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bought it at a shop by Glover Garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.75,0:14:34.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I've been waiting for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.54,0:14:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.32,0:14:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Delicious! It's the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.48,0:14:43.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really tasty, right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.06,0:14:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.61,0:14:49.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you going to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.49,0:15:00.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, actually, a few days ago, Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} was almost hit by a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.13,0:15:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.50,0:15:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said that he thought someone pushed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.69,0:15:09.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.02,0:15:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you mention it earlier?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.38,0:15:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.93,0:15:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} might've disappeared because he thought his life was in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.92,0:15:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the end, we didn't find any usable clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.30,0:15:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.00,0:15:37.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Futaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.68,0:15:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.46,0:16:03.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We lost him...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.33,0:16:09.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why was she running so desperately?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.60,0:16:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.37,0:16:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Ōki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.90,0:16:26.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} sent part two of the script in an e-mail?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.35,0:16:29.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And is the culprit's name in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.06,0:16:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? It's still not finished?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.70,0:16:42.91,Signs,,0,0,0,,Dejima
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.16,0:16:47.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.49,0:16:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.24,0:16:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Somehow...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.55,0:17:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's strange, they were fixed in place...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.25,0:17:02.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.26,0:17:06.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so, that was amazing, young lady. Was that karate?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.98,0:17:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though she may not look it, she won the Kantō Tournament. She's the Champion!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.45,0:17:26.74,Signs,,0,0,0,,Trading Post Chief's House
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.73,0:17:25.42,Thoughts,,10,10,15,,{\be10}The second part of script that was e-mailed was also unfinished.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.42,0:17:29.02,Thoughts,,0,0,15,,{\be10}And in it, a second murder was depicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.62,0:17:32.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The crime scene was the Dejima Trading Post Chief's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.32,0:17:35.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The victim was a spy employed by the Nagasaki magistrate's office,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.88,0:17:40.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and he left the kanji numeral nine as a dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.09,0:17:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what'd he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.48,0:17:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For further information, ask the daughter of the Miura shipping agency, O-Tei.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.89,0:17:52.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cut! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.16,0:17:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though we've ended up with no holes in the schedule, the problem is what to do now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.81,0:18:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.49,0:18:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without any foreshadowing, a new character's suddenly appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.11,0:18:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The character has lots of puzzling lines, and I think it's an important role, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.35,0:18:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't have any actor to play the character, nor time or money to bring someone from Tōkyō.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.62,0:18:16.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a disaster!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.04,0:18:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, a disast—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.40,0:18:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You, how old are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.22,0:18:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm seventeen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.14,0:18:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! That's what we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.50,0:18:29.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.86,0:18:32.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're borrowing this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.77,0:18:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're kidding! I can't do this! It's too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.92,0:18:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I won't! I won't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.86,0:18:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Help me, Dad, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.45,0:18:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.87,0:18:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.11,0:18:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! It's the wrong way up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.39,0:18:49.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amateurs are so useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.53,0:18:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.78,0:18:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.45,0:18:54.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, will this really work?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.93,0:18:57.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't some school's art festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.21,0:18:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.97,0:19:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you can at least say your lines, we'll take care of the rest somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.46,0:19:05.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, r-r-r-right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.63,0:19:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, try practising your lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.49,0:19:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can start off by looking at the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.74,0:19:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! Wait a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.65,0:19:15.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, start!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.17,0:19:18.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-S-Sakamoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, I-I am the daughter of the Miura family, O-Tei.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.47,0:19:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What may I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:28.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, isn't that a 'dress', like a Western girl would wear?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.53,0:19:32.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The daughter of the Miura family is famous throughout town for wearing exotic{lit. Spanish or Portuguese} clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.55,0:19:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, the man in the Trading Post Chief's House.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.30,0:19:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He left behind the number nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.70,0:19:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know anything about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.38,0:19:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nine?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.31,0:19:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Numbers are important.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.38,0:19:49.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.20,0:19:48.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Numbers will solve everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes, Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.48,0:19:55.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why me too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.22,0:19:57.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cut! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.48,0:20:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.23,0:20:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a weird line.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.66,0:20:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Numbers will solve everything.'
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.19,0:20:13.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, a lot of the actors in the production have numbers in their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.39,0:20:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Andrew Ha{\c}tta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who plays Glover has one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.39,0:20:17.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}8
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.62,0:20:21.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}1000
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.62,0:20:21.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Playing his wife, Tsuru, is Benichi{\c}yo Yamashita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.58,0:20:26.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}7
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.58,0:20:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. Futaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s surname is Nana{\c}o too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.25,0:20:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's some in the staff too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.30,0:20:33.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}3
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.30,0:20:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ōki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s name is Taizō{\c}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.06,0:20:35.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}1
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.06,0:20:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s is Kazu{\c}omi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.35,0:20:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakamoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.31,0:20:45.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a demon living here in Nakashima River.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.19,0:20:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.15,0:20:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you need not worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.11,0:20:54.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The demon's weak point is the second tooth from the left in its lower jaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.07,0:20:56.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cut! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.49,0:20:59.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The demon's weak point...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.10,0:21:00.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yet another puzzling line.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.25,0:21:03.14,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.60,0:21:06.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The font changes just for this line.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.29,0:21:07.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could this mean...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.64,0:21:18.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could these lines be a message from Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.10,0:21:24.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And if O-Tei of the Miura family is a character created to convey that message...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.18,0:21:28.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then it must be about the reason for his disappearance!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.39,0:21:29.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.86,0:21:30.86,Signs,,0,0,0,,Serial Art Theft Case
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.37,0:21:42.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is all that I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.49,0:21:46.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, next I'll guide you to the first ever Western-style restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.72,0:21:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've had enough! Let me out of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.00,0:22:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was probably punched. And with bare hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.73,0:22:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on! Sakota!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.69,0:22:08.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the ambulance?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.06,0:22:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've called it! It'll be here soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.07,0:22:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it! Who got you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.31,0:22:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.10,0:22:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.33,0:22:25.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.18,0:22:27.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I-It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.29,0:22:29.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The karate champion?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.13,0:22:32.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.01,0:22:36.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Sakota! Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.43,0:22:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakota!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.92,0:24:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.52,0:24:05.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just about to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.07,0:24:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the viewing platform... I was suddenly attacked by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.36,0:24:10.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it! I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.05,0:24:12.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The meaning of the dying message is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.41,0:24:15.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who attacked Sakota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.65,0:24:19.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it was you, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.41,0:24:25.42,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,On the next Conan: 'The Nagasaki Mystery Theatre (Present Day Case)'!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.42,0:24:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Kanji Stroke Order!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.42,0:25:00.22,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.42,0:24:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a1}Dad, when did I—?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.20,0:24:33.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a1}Sleeping Ran, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.34,0:24:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a1}I'll save you for sure.
